<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-01T06:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-01T06:30:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/661: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Singapore</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Patton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Singapore</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-01T19:00:00+07:30">December
                                    1, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 1—9:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>327. Governor today issued a proclamation declaring state of emergency
                            and calling out military, naval and air volunteer forces of Straits
                            Settlements. Military authorities issued statement at the <pb facs="0375" n="365" xml:id="pg_365"/> same time stressing that this
                            does not signify immediate deterioration of the situation but is only
                            precautionary step permitting mobilization to be effected without undue
                            dislocation of civil activities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Patton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>